\par So, first, I think it would be useful to make a distinction between two broad categories: 
\par Content-related\line or\line Content-driven and Interaction-driven 
\par Most content driven sites maintain
 reasonable ethical standards, roughly comparable to the "real" or "non-virtual" media. This is because many of these sites were established by businesses with a "real" dimension to start with (Walt Disney, The Economist, etc.). These sites (at least the 
institutional ones) maintain standards of privacy, veracity, cross-checking of information, etc. 
\par Personal home pages would be a sub-category of content-driven sites. These cannot be seriously considered "media". They are representatives of the new phenomen
